			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">blargg wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Disch, perhaps we could rename the APU's frame counter the beat counter? Decay timer? Note timer? I'm all for better terms.</div><br />Probably "APU tick counter" because the function seems to be analogous to that of MOD/S3M/XM/IT ticks, or "APU update timer".<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">I'd call the length counters duration counters, the frequency registers period registers, since raising the value lowers the frequency (unlike on the Game Boy, where they are frequency values).</div>
<br />Game Boy registers are not frequency values; they're negative period values because the Game Boy period divider is an up counter, unlike the down counters in the NES. For instance, an octave series on Game Boy goes 0, 1024, 1536, 1792, 1920, for period 2048-x and frequency 131072/(2048-x) Hz: 64, 128, 256, 512, 1024 Hz.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

